{"title_page": "List of warships by nickname", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThe following is a list of [[warship]]s listed by [[nickname]]. See below for a key to abbreviations.\n\n{{compact ToC|side=yes|top=yes|num=yes}}\n\n==A==\n* \"Abe\" \u2013 '''[[USS Abraham Lincoln (CVN-72)|USS ''Abraham Lincoln'']]''''<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20051218093115/http://www.news.navy.mil/search/display.asp?story_id=13848]</ref> [[Abraham Lincoln]] is often informally referred to as \"Abe\" or \"Stink'n Lincoln\"\n*\"Ageless Warrior\" \u2013 '''[[USS Coral Sea (CV-43)|USS ''Coral Sea'']]'''<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20041228072024/http://www.cnsl.spear.navy.mil/jamesewilliams/WILLIAMS/cmc.htm]</ref><ref>[http://www.usscoralsea.net/]</ref>\n*\"Aggie\" \u2013 '''[[HMS Agamemnon (1906)|HMS ''Agamemnon'']]'''<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070926235019/http://royalnavy.mod.uk/server/show/conWebDoc.1268/changeNav/3533]</ref>\n*\"Aggie on Horseback\" \u2013 '''[[Shoreham-class sloop|HMS ''Weston'']]''';<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070926235019/http://royalnavy.mod.uk/server/show/conWebDoc.1268/changeNav/3533]</ref> nickname named for [[Agnes Weston]], a [[Temperance movement|temperance]] and [[sailor]]'s advocate; \"on horseback\" is a jocular mistranslation of [[Latin language|Latin]] ''\"super-mare\"'' (\"on the sea\"), ''\"mare\"'' being equated with a female horse\n*\"'A Gin Court\" \u2013 '''[[HMS Agincourt|HMS ''Agincourt'']]'''; Battleship seized from Turkey in 1914; because of its luxurious Turkish outfit\n*\"Algonquatraz\" \u2013 '''[[HMCS Algonquin (DDG 283)|HMCS ''Algonquin'' (DDG 283)]]'''\n*\"'Am and Tripe\" \u2013 '''[[HMS Amphitrite (1898)|HMS ''Amphitrite'']]''';<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070926235019/http://royalnavy.mod.uk/server/show/conWebDoc.1268/changeNav/3533]</ref> humorous malapropism\n*\"America's Favorite Carrier\" \u2013 '''[[USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70)|USS ''Carl Vinson'']]'''<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060906043244/http://www.cvn70.navy.mil/presrel/18NOV04_Vinson%20Birthday.html]</ref>\n*\"Angry Cat\" \u2013 '''[[French battleship Henri IV|French ship ''Henri IV'']]''';<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060509160813/http://www.royal-navy.mod.uk/server/show/nav.3818]</ref> named so by the British, a play on the pronunciation of \"Henri Quatre\"\n*\"Archdeacon\" \u2013 '''[[HMS Venerable (1899)|HMS ''Venerable'']]''';<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070926235019/http://royalnavy.mod.uk/server/show/conWebDoc.1268/changeNav/3533]</ref> a play on the phrase \"venerable archdeacon\"\n*\"Athabee\" \u2013 '''[[HMCS Athabaskan (DDG 282)|HMCS ''Athabaskan'' (DDG 282)]]'''\n\n==B==\n*\"Babe Lincoln\" \u2013 '''[[USS Abraham Lincoln (CVN-72)|USS ''Abraham Lincoln'']]'''; reference to her 1995 deployment, the first United States warship to put to sea with women in combat roles\n*\"Battle Cat\" \u2013 '''[[USS Kitty Hawk (CV-63)|USS ''Kitty Hawk'']]'''<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20051129002924/http://www.news.navy.mil/search/display.asp?story_id=12115]</ref>\n*\"Battle Schmoozer\", \"Belcrash\" \u2013 '''[[USS Belknap (CG-26)|USS ''Belknap'']]'''; reference her collision with the USS ''Kennedy'' in 1975\n*\"Battle Star\" \u2013 '''{{USS|Carl Vinson|CVN-70}}\n*\"Big Ben\" \u2013 '''[[USS Franklin (CV-13)|USS ''Franklin'']]''';<ref>[http://www.ussfranklin.org]</ref> the ship is named after [[Benjamin Franklin]]\n*\"Big D\" \u2013 '''{{USS|Dallas|SSN-700|6}}'''; given to the boat to denote being named in honor of the [[Dallas, Texas|city of Dallas]].\n*\"The Big E\" \u2013 '''{{USS|Enterprise|CV-6|6}}''' (CV-6)<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060427021258/http://www.chinfo.navy.mil/navpalib/ships/carriers/histories/cv06-enterprise/cv06-enterprise.html]</ref> and '''[[USS Enterprise (CVN-65)|USS ''Enterprise'']]''' (CVN-65)<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060427092124/http://www.chinfo.navy.mil/navpalib/ships/carriers/histories/cv65-enterprise/cv65-enterprise.html]</ref>\n*\"The Big J\" \u2013 '''[[USS New Jersey (BB-62)|USS ''New Jersey'']]'''<ref>[http://www.ussnewjersey.com/]</ref>\n*\"Big John\" \u2013 '''[[USS John F. Kennedy (CV-67)|USS ''John F. Kennedy'']]'''<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060624094755/http://www.nol.navy.mil/homepages/cv67/]</ref>\n*\"Big Lizzie\" \u2013 '''{{HMS|Queen Elizabeth|1913|6}}'''<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070926235019/http://royalnavy.mod.uk/server/show/conWebDoc.1268/changeNav/3533]</ref>\n*\"Big Mamie\" \u2013  '''[[USS Massachusetts (BB-59)|USS ''Massachusetts'']]'''<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20061207083427/http://www.chinfo.navy.mil/navpalib/ships/battleships/massachusetts/bb59-mass.html]</ref>\n*\"The Big Nasty\" \u2013 '''{{USS|Nassau|LHA-4|6}}'''\n*\"The Big Stick\" \u2013 '''[[USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71)|USS ''Theodore Roosevelt'']]''';<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060616054333/http://www.tr.surfor.navy.mil/default.aspx]</ref> based on [[Theodore Roosevelt]]'s quotation, \"Speak softly and carry a big stick\".<ref>[https://www.loc.gov/exhibits/treasures/trm139.html]</ref> Also used for the {{USS|Iowa|BB-61|6}} for its role as the '''Big Stick of the Pacific''' during most of the naval battles it participated in.\n*\"Big Gray Deuce\" \u2013 '''[[USS Essex (LHD-2)|USS ''Essex'']]'''; humorous malapropism\n*\"Billy Ruffian\" \u2013 '''[[HMS Bellerophon (1907)|HMS ''Bellerophon'']]''';<ref>[http://royalnavy.mod.uk]</ref> humorous mispronunciation\n*\"The Black Dragon\" \u2013 '''{{USS|New Jersey|BB-62|6}}'''\n*\"The Blue Ghost\" \u2013 '''{{USS|Lexington|CV-16}}'''; nickname supposedly bestowed by Japanese radio propagandist [[Tokyo Rose]] because of the color of her camouflage painting and because she repeatedly disproved reports that she had been sunk<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060426190524/http://militaryhistory.about.com/od/navalwarfare/a/blueghost.htm]</ref>\n*\"Bonnie\" \u2013 '''[[HMCS Bonaventure (CVL 22)|HMCS ''Bonaventure'']]'''<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060510134926/http://www.airforce.forces.gc.ca/equip/historical/bonaventurelst_e.asp]</ref>\n*\"Bonnie Dick\" \u2013 '''[[USS Bon Homme Richard (CV-31)|USS ''Bom Homme Richard'' CV/CVA-31]]''' and '''[[USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6)|USS ''Bomhomme Richard'' (LHD-6)]]'''\n*\"Buckin' Bronco\" \u2013 '''[[USS Colorado (BB-45)|USS ''Colorado (BB-45)'']]'''\n*\"Building (hull number)\" \u2013 a U.S. Navy joke about ships that don't go to sea much.\n**\"Building 575\" \u2013 '''[[USS Seawolf (SSN-575)|USS ''Seawolf'' (SSN-575)]]'''\n**\"Building 597\" \u2013  '''[[USS Tullibee (SSN-597)|USS ''Tullibee'' (SSN-597)]]'''\n**\"Building 21\" \u2013 '''[[USS Seawolf (SSN-21)|USS ''Seawolf'' (SSN-21)]]'''\n**\"Building 11\" \u2013 '''[[USS Coronado (AGF-11)|USS ''Coronado'' (AGF-11)]]'''\n*\"Bulldog of the Navy\" \u2013 '''[[USS Oregon (BB-3)|USS ''Oregon'' (BB-3)]]'''\n*\"The Big Risk\" \u2013 '''[[USS Oriskany (CV-34)|USS ''Oriskany (CV-34)]]'''\n*\"Bag Lady\" \u2013 '''[[USS Bagley (FF-1069)|USS ''Bagley (FF-1069)'']]'''; humorous malaproprism\n*\"Berzerkly\" \u2013 '''[[USS Berkeley (DDG-15)|USS ''Berkeley (DDG-15)'']]'''; humorous malaproprism\n*\"Broke\" \u2013 '''[[USS Brooke (FFG-1)|USS ''Brooke (FFG-1)'']]'''; humorous malaproprism\n\n==C==\n*\"C-ville\" \u2013 '''[[USS Chancellorsville (CG-62)|USS ''Chancellorsville'']]'''\n*\"Cannabis\" \u2013 '''[[USS Canopus (AS-34)|USS ''Canopus'']]'''; humorous malapropism\n*\"Can o\u2019 Pus\" \u2013 '''USS ''Canopus''''' (1980s reference to first 20% female crew.)\n*\"Can Opener\" \u2013 '''[[USS John F. Kennedy (CV-67)|USS ''John F. Kennedy'']]''', after collision with USS ''Belknap''\n*\"Century One\" \u2013 '''[[HMS Centurion (1911)|HMS ''Centurion'']]'''; humorous malapropism\n*\"Cheer Up Ship\" \u2013 '''[[USS Nevada (BB-36)|USS ''Nevada (BB-36)'']]'''\n*\u201dChesapeake Raider\u201d - '''[[USS Wyoming (BB-32)|USS ''Wyoming (BB-32)'']]''', nickname given after frequent sightings of the ship in the Chesapeake Bay during World War Two.\n*\"Christmas Anthem\" \u2013 '''[[HMS Chrysanthemum (1917)|HMS ''Chrysanthemum'']]'''; humorous malapropism\n*\"Chuckie V\" \u2013 '''[[USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70)|USS ''Carl Vinson'']]'''\n*\"Cocoa Boat\" \u2013 '''[[HMS Curacoa (D41)|HMS ''Curacoa'']]'''; humorous malapropism\n*\"Connie\" \u2013 '''[[USS Constellation (CV-64)|USS ''Constellation'']]'''; diminutive of ship's name\n*\"The Count\" \u2013 '''[[USS Comte de Grasse (DD-974)|USS ''Comte de Grasse'']]'''; named for [[Fran\u00e7ois Joseph Paul, marquis de Grasetilly, comte de Grasse|Comte de Grasse]] ([[French language|French]], \"Count de Grasse\"), an ally of the Americans in the [[American War of Independence]]\n*\"Curious\" \u2013 '''{{HMS|Furious|47|6}}'''<ref>[http://www.royal-navy.org/shiplist/index.php?option=com_content&task=section&id=5&Itemid=13]{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n*\"Cellblock 70\" \u2013 '''[[USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70)|USS ''Carl Vinson'']]'''; humorous reference to restricted liberty for crew after incidents in Bremerton, WA, in the mid-1980s.\n\n==D==\n*\"Despair Ship Remorse\" \u2013 '''[[HMS Resource (F79)|HMS ''Resource'']]''';<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060509160813/http://www.royal-navy.mod.uk/server/show/nav.3818]</ref> humorous malapropism on \"Repair ship ''Resource''\"\n*\"Decrepit\" \u2013 '''{{USS|Intrepid|CV-11|6}}'''\n*\"Dirty Cush\" \u2013 '''{{USS|Cushing|DD-985|6}}'''\n*\"Dirty Two-Thirty\" \u2013 '''[[HMCS Margaree (DDE 230)|HMCS ''Margaree'' (DDE 230)]]''' (decommissioned); from her hull number.\n*\"Dirty V\" \u2013 '''[[USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70)|USS ''Carl Vinson'']]'''; humorous malapropism\n*\"Dreado\" \u2013 '''[[HMS Dreadnought (1906)|HMS ''Dreadnought'']]''';<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060509160813/http://www.royal-navy.mod.uk/server/show/nav.3818]</ref> diminutive of ship's name\n*\"Dull Ass\" \u2013 '''[[USS Dallas (SSN-700)|USS ''Dallas'']]''';