{"title_page": "Danielle Campbell", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{short description|American actress}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Danielle Campbell\n| image              = Danielle Campbell at PaleyFest 2014.jpg\n| caption            = Campbell at [[PaleyFest]] in 2014 for ''[[The Originals (TV series)|The Originals]]''\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1995|1|30}}\n| birth_name         = <!--Don't need since it's same as main name-->\n| birth_place        = [[Hinsdale, Illinois]], United States\n| occupation         = Actress, model\n| years_active       = 2006\u2013present\n| notable_works      = ''[[The Originals (TV series)|The Originals]]''<br/>''[[Tell Me a Story (TV series)|Tell Me a Story]]''\n}}\n\n'''Danielle Marie Campbell'''<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Danielle Campbell |user=daniellemcam |number=631831729565659137 |title=@TruthVRA Danielle Marie Campbell \ud83d\udc8b |date=August 13, 2015 |accessdate=May 9, 2018}}</ref> (born January 30,<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Danielle Campbell |user=daniellemcam |number=163992243571654656 |title=Thank you so much for all the happy birthdays guys!!! It means so much to me love you! Xoxoxoxo |date=January 30, 2012 |accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref> 1995<ref name=\"Chicagotribune\" /><ref name=\"Hollywoodlife\">{{cite web |url=http://hollywoodlife.com/celeb/danielle-campbell/ |title=Danielle Campbell |work=Hollywoodlife.com |accessdate=March 29, 2015}}</ref>) is an American actress. She is known for her starring roles as Jessica Olson in the 2010 [[Disney Channel Original Movie]] ''[[Starstruck (2010 film)|StarStruck]]'', Simone Daniels in the 2011 Disney film ''[[Prom (film)|Prom]]'', Davina Claire in the 2013 [[The CW|CW]] television drama series ''[[The Originals (TV series)|The Originals]]'' and Kayla Powell in the 2018 [[CBS All Access]] television [[psychological thriller]] series ''[[Tell Me a Story (TV series)|Tell Me a Story]]''.\n\n== Early life ==\nCampbell is from [[Hinsdale, Illinois|Hinsdale]], [[Illinois]]. Her parents are Georganne and John Campbell, and she has a younger brother.<ref name=\"Chicagotribune\">{{cite web |url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2011-04-26/entertainment/ct-live-0427-danielle-campbell-prom-20110426_1_teen-movie-selena-gomez-danielle-campbell |title=Hey, you're grounded |work=[[Chicago Tribune]] |author=Nina Metz |date=April 26, 2011 |accessdate=March 19, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Chicagotribune 2\">{{cite web |url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/ct-danielle-campbell-the-originals-20141006-story.html#page=1 |title='Originals' actress goes from Hinsdale to Hollywood |work=[[Chicago Tribune]] |author=Courtney Crowder |date=October 5, 2014 |accessdate=March 22, 2015}}</ref> She was discovered in a hair salon in [[Chicago]] at the age of 10.<ref name=\"Chicagotribune\"/><ref name=\"Missoandfriends\">{{cite web|url=http://www.missoandfriends.com/interviews/danielle-campbell-interview.php |title=Danielle Campbell interview on Miss O & Friends |work=Missoandfriends.com |accessdate=April 3, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150407115907/http://www.missoandfriends.com/interviews/danielle-campbell-interview.php |archivedate=April 7, 2015 }}</ref><ref name=\"Hitfix\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hitfix.com/starr-raving/interview-the-originals-danielle-campbell-talks-life-death-and-marcel |title=Interview: 'The Originals' ' Danielle Campbell talks life, death and Marcel |work=Hitfix.com |author=Liane Bonin Starr |date=April 15, 2014 |accessdate=March 24, 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nCampbell's first acting role was as a guest star in five episodes of ''[[Prison Break]].''<ref name=\"Hollywoodlife\" /><ref name=\"Chicagotribune 2\" /> She also appeared in a nationwide commercial for [[Build-A-Bear Workshop]]<ref name=\"Chicagotribune\" /><ref name=\"Chicagotribune 2\" /> and played the character of Darla in the 2008 movie ''The Poker House''. In 2010, she appeared in the Disney Channel television series ''[[Zeke and Luther]]''<ref name=\"Hollywoodlife\" /> as Dani, before starring in the television movie ''[[Starstruck (2010 film)|StarStruck]]'' with [[Sterling Knight]] the same year.<ref name=\"Chicagotribune\" /><ref name=\"Chicagotribune 2\" /> Upon ''StarStruck'''s release, she signed a development deal with Disney. She starred in the movie ''[[Prom (film)|Prom]]'', released on April 29, 2011, co-starring with [[Nicholas Braun]], [[Nolan Sotillo]], and [[Aimee Teegarden]].<ref name=\"Chicagotribune\"/>\n\nIn 2013, she was cast in a starring role on the television series ''[[The Originals (TV series)|The Originals]]''<ref name=\"Thenewpotato\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thenewpotato.com/2014/12/08/danielle-campbell/|title=Danielle Campbell: On Kickboxing, Sunscreen, And Apples With Peanut Butter|date=December 8, 2014|work=Thenewpotato.com|accessdate=March 27, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Nellie Andreeva |url=http://deadline.com/2013/02/danielle-campbell-joins-vampire-diaries-spinoff-chin-han-to-recur-on-arrow-426237/ |title=Danielle Campbell Joins \u2018Vampire Diaries\u2019 Spinoff, Chin Han To Recur On \u2018Arrow\u2019 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=February 8, 2013 |accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref> as a powerful sixteen-year-old witch named Davina.<ref name=\"Chicagotribune 2\"/><ref name=\"Hitfix\"/> In late 2013, producers of the 2015 film ''16 South'' announced that Campbell would star in the film alongside [[Luke Benward]].<ref name=\"Chicagotribune 2\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hopekelley.com/16southmovie.html |title=OFFICIAL WEBSITE FOR \"16 South\" |work=Hopekelley.com |accessdate=March 19, 2015}}</ref> In April 2015, Campbell shot the movie ''Race To Redemption'' in which she starred alongside Aiden Flowers and Luke Perry; the movie was released in 2016. Campbell was also cast as Ellie Reed in the 2016 television series ''SINs'', and Maddy in the 2017 [[Fine Brothers]] production ''F the Prom''. In March 2018, she appeared in the music video for \"Better With You\" by [[Jesse McCartney]].\n\nIn 2018 Campbell had a recurring role in the second season of the [[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]] television series ''[[Famous in Love]]''. In June 2018 she was cast in a starring role in the [[CBS All Access]] television drama series ''[[Tell Me a Story (TV series)|Tell Me a Story]]''.<ref name=\"TMaS\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/tell-me-a-story-danielle-campbell-to-star-in-kevin-williamsons-cbs-all-access-drama-series-1202404310/|title=\u2018Tell Me A Story\u2019: Danielle Campbell To Star In Kevin Williamson\u2019s CBS All Access Drama Series|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=June 5, 2018|access-date=June 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nCampbell lives in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://danielle-campbell.org/category/interviews/|title=interviews \u00ab  Danielle Campbell Web|website=danielle-campbell.org|access-date=October 29, 2017}}</ref> In November 2015, Campbell started dated former One Direction member, Louis Tomlinson. They broke up a year later.\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Film roles\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2008\n| data-sort-value=\"Poker House, The\" | ''[[The Poker House]]''\n| Darla\n|\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Prom (film)|Prom]]''\n| Simone Daniels\n| \n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Madea's Witness Protection]]''\n| Cindy Needleman\n| \n|-\n| 2016\n| ''Race to Redemption''\n| Hannah Rhodes\n| \n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[F the Prom]]''\n| Maddy Datner\n| Direct-to-video film\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Shrimp (film)|Shrimp]]''\n| Jess' date\n| Short film\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[Being Frank]]''\n|Allison\n|\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Television roles\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2006\u20132007\n| ''[[Prison Break]]''\n| Gracey Hollander\n| 4 episodes\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Zeke and Luther]]''\n| Dani